page.title: 18COUNTY ELECTIONS IN BURWELL.
page.content: Most people aren't interested in the {County Council Elections.}They think whoever they vote for won't do enough for them. At the{Liberal Committee Room they have lists with streets arranged alphabetically. Numbers from the polling station go to the committee room and if they are on one of the lists there they are crossed off.A list of numbers comes every hour. {Polling stations}for this division were in Burwell, Reach, Bottisham, Lode,Swaffham Prior and Swaffham Bulbeck. Votes were counted in Ely.{The {Liberal/S.D.P Alliance won}by 191 votes from the{Conservatives. 3239 or about{50%}of people who could have{voted}did so.
